[[File:KonpiraHonkyou2010.jpg|thumb|right|Headquarters of Kotohira Hongyō]] '''Kotohira Hongyō''' (金刀比羅本教) is a religious organization established as a religious corporation on {{ill|August 5, 1969|ja|昭和44年8月5日}}, with its headquarters at {{ill|Kotohira-gū|ja|金刀比羅宮|1=Kotohira-gū}} in {{ill|Nakatado District, Kagawa|ja|香川県仲多度郡}}.
== Overview == The main deity worshipped is the '''Kotohira Great Deity''' (金刀比羅大神), and the organization reveres as its founder the fourth abbot of Mount Zōzu's Konpira Daigongen temple, Kongōbō Yūjō, who is deified as '''Iwasaka no Mikoto''' (厳魂彦命). The organization aims to modernize the {{ill|Konpira pilgrimage societies|ja|金毘羅講}} from the medieval and early modern periods and to reorganize the faith groups and associations devoted to Kotohira since the {{ill|Meiji Restoration|ja|明治維新}}. Conversion is required for membership<ref>{{教団データベース|177}}</ref>.
A regular publication titled *Kotohira* is issued by the organization.
== Scriptures == * The Five Articles of the Constitution of Kotohira Hongyō * 20 Articles of Practical Principles * {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記}} * {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}}
== Five Articles of the Constitution of Kotohira Hongyō == * Never forget that one’s life is deeply connected to the divine ancestors of the past and will continue eternally through one’s descendants.<ref name=gojo>[http://www.konpira.or.jp/about/center/main/center.html Kotohira Hongyō]</ref> * Since one is also a manifestation of the divine, daily purification practices must be diligently performed to maintain purity and integrity of both mind and body.<ref name=gojo/> * Refrain from expressing discontent. Address all matters with gratitude and joy toward the divine blessings.<ref name=gojo/> * To achieve unity between humans and the divine, one must adhere to clarity, honesty, and righteousness.<ref name=gojo/> * All people are destined to become deities, and one must strive daily to become a greater deity.<ref name=gojo/>
== References == {{reflist|2}}
== Related Articles == * {{ill|Konpira Gongen|ja|金毘羅権現}}
== External Links == * [http://www.konpira.or.jp/ Kotohira Hongyō Official Website]
{{New religions in Japan}}
